  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until beginning to blister, once done, remove the tray from the oven and set aside</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634048244275-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634048244275-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634048244275-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634048244275-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1634048244275-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced red onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634048282230-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634048282230-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634048282230-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634048282230-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1634048282230-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, combine your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and<strong> soft cheese </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min</p><p>Add the <strong>creamy stock</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and cook, covered, over a high heat for 5-6 min or until the squash has begun to soften – this is your <strong>squash & tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
